Name: datafile_name
Description: File name of EEG data

Name: subject_id
Description: Subject ID

Name: task
Description: FACE, MMN, RS, VEP

Name: line_noise
Description: Estimate of how much electrical line noise is present in the EEG signal Values of 1 indicate no line noise, values of 0 indicate pure line noise

Name: reference_for_faster
Description: Reference electrode used by the FASTER algorithm used for bad channel detection (Nolan et al, 2010)

Name: faster_bad_channels
Description: List of channels identified by FASTER algorithm as being artifactual, or not representative of brain activity

Name: ica_prep_bad_channels
Description: Channels deleted by FASTER before ICA

Name: length_ica_data
Description: Amount of continuous data (in seconds) used for independent component analysis

Name: total_ics
Description: Number of independent components identified by ICA

Name: ics_removed
Description: Independent components removed by adjusted-ADJUST (Leach et al, 2020)

Name: total_epochs_pre_artifact_rej
Description: Number of epochs collected

Name: total_epochs_post_artifact_rej
Description: Number of epochs retained after epoch-level artifact rejection

Name: total_channels_interp
Description: Number of channels interpolated using spline interpolation after bad channel removal

Name: avg_chan_interp_artifact_rej
Description: Average number of channels interpolated per epoch using spline interpolation for each task

Name: std_chan_interp_artifact_rej
Description: Standard deviation of the number of channels removed per epoch for each task

Name: range_chan_interp_artifact_rej
Description: Range of number of channels interpolated per epoch

Name: boundary_marker
Description: If the specified string is present in the EEG events, data from before this marker was removed prior to analysis

Name: ekg_channels
Description: Non-cortical electrodes measuring the electrocardiogram

Name: channel_locations
Description: The path to the *sfp file with electrode channel locations

Name: down_sample
Description: Whether data were downsampled

Name: sampling_rate
Description: The new sampling rate after downsampling Only used if down_sample = 1

Name: delete_outerlayer
Description: Whether outer layer of channels was removed

Name: outerlayer_channel
Description: List of removed outer layer channels Only used if delete_outerlayer = 1

Name: highpass
Description: High-pass filter cutoff frequency

Name: lowpass
Description: Low-pass filter cutoff frequency

Name: remove_baseline
Description: Whether baseline period was removed

Name: baseline_window
Description: Baseline time window

Name: voltthresh_rejection
Description: Whether epochs were removed based on voltage thresholds

Name: volt_threshold
Description: Negative and positive values in uV used for epoch thresholding

Name: interp_epoch
Description: Whether interpolation was used for channels removed at the epoch level

Name: frontal_channels
Description: List of frontal channels

Name: interp_channels
Description: Whether to interpolation was used for channels fully removed

Name: rerefer_data
Description: Whether data were re-referenced

Name: reref
Description: Either [] for electrode average re-referencing or list of electrodes used for re-referencing

Name: output_format
Description: 1 = set; 2 = mat

Name: roi_of_interest
Description: Selects the ROI for ERPs

Name: pre_Latency
Description: The amount of time (in seconds) to include in an epoch prior to the event specified by the entries in marker_names

Name: post_Latency
Description: The amount of time (in seconds) to include in an epoch following the event specified by the entries in marker_names

Name: erp_window_start
Description: Time window of interest in the topographic plots and the averages for the mat files

Name: erp_window_end
Description: Time window of interest in the topographic plots and the averages for the mat files

Name: erp_filter
Description: Boolean variable indicating whether to apply a second low-pass filter before creating ERPs

Name: erp_lowpass
Description: The frequency at which to apply the second low-pass filter

Name: marker_names
Description: Name of event code markers you want to construct epochs around (eg, DIN3) If make_dummy_events = true, then this should instead represent the first marker in your EEG file Dummy events will then be placed after the first instance of this marker

Name: score_times1
Description: Sets of time windows that are used for participants between 3-6 months. Used for computation of standardized measurement error, peak/adaptive mean amplitude within the time window, and mean amplitude across the time window

Name: score_times2
Description: Sets of time windows that are used for participants between 6-9 months. Used for computation of standardized measurement error, peak/adaptive mean amplitude within the time window, and mean amplitude across the time window

Name: score_rois
Description: Names of each ROI used with score_times for computation of standardized measurement error, mean amplitude, and peak/adaptive mean amplitude

Name: make_dummy_events
Description: Resting state ony: Dummy events were inserted into the data This option is used to create new events in resting state acquisitions where there are no triggers to denote epochs

Name: num_dummy_events
Description: Resting state only: The number of dummy events created Only used if make_dummy_events = true

Name: dummy_event_spacing
Description: Resting state only: The amount of time (in seconds) between dummy events Note that epochs are constructed around events, so this isn’t the same as spacing between epochs

Name: score_ages
Description: Sets of age bins used to define time_windows for ERP measures and SME

Name: condition
Description: Stimulus condition: inverted, object, uprightInv, uprightObj in the Faces task.

Name: condition
Description: Stimulus condition: standard, deviant, predeviant in the MMN task.

Name: Latency_<time-window>_<ROI>
Description: Latency to peak/adaptive mean amplitude within specified time window (in ms) at the specified region of interest. Values are averaged across trials for each condition.

Name: ntrials
Description: Number of trials per condition retained after processing.

Name: MeanAmp_<time-window>_<ROI>
Description: Mean amplitude within specified time window (in ms) at the specified region of interest. Values are averaged across trials for each condition.

Name: Peak_<time-window>_<ROI>
Description: Peak/adpative mean amplitude within specified time window (in ms) at the specified region of interest. Values are averaged across trials for each condition.

Name: SME_<time-window>_<ROI>
Description: Standardized measurement error within specified time window (in ms) at the specified region of interest. Values are averaged across trials for each condition.

Name: Latency_<time-window>_<ROI>
Description: Latency to peak/adaptive mean amplitude within specified time window (in ms) at the specified region of interest. Values are provided for each trial.

Name: MeanAmplitude_<time-window>_<ROI>
Description: Mean amplitude within specified time window (in ms) at the specified region of interest. Values are provided for each trial.

Name: condition
Description: Stimulus condition: VEP has only one condition.

Name: id
Description: Subject ID

Name: condition
Description: Stimulus condition: standard, deviant, predeviant in the MMN task.

Name: Peak_<time-window>_<ROI>
Description: Peak/adpative mean amplitude within specified time window (in ms) at the specified region of interest. Values are provided for each trial.

Name: trial_num
Description: Trial number

Name: frequency
Description: 1 Hz bins from 1-50 Hz in the resting state task.

Name: SME
Description: Standardized measurement error in each frequency bin in the resting state task.

Name: mean_power
Description: Mean power in each frequency bin in the resting state task.

Name: id
Description: Subject ID in the resting state task.

Name: spectra_output_row
Description: Electrode label

Name: spectra_output_1.0Hz
Description: Absolute power from 0.3-1Hz at corresponding electrode site

Name: spectra_output_2.0Hz
Description: Absolute power from1-2Hz at corresponding electrode site

Name: spectra_output_3.0Hz
Description: Absolute power from 2-3Hz at corresponding electrode site
